As a professional golfer, he has earned prize money totalling £9.4million.

And yesterday, Ian Poulter was accused of being 'out of touch with reality' after complaining that his wife was forced to look after their children without a nanny.

The 38-year-old sportsman, who has won two world championships, had booked six business class seats with British Airways, for his wife Katie, their four children and their nanny.

